commit.message:
Remove useless guard around PY_SSIZE_T_CLEAN

PY_MAJOR_VERSION is not defined yet before including Python.h,
effectively preventing PY_SSIZE_T_CLEAN from getting defined.

Allow about 96k of command line

Close #52.
Declare Python 3.9 supported
Added black configuration
setup blacker than black
Added test to verify behaviour with long environment

Added getthreadtitle(), setthreadtitle()

Close #54
Dropped outdated section about other references

Tag the tests building the embedded program for testing

They are more prone to failures than others. They can be skipped with::

    pytest -m "not embedded"

Delay module initialisation to the first use

It opens the risk of failing initialisation if it's not used early, but
as I'm growing older I'm valuing more and more modules without import
side effects.

Added note about initialising the module early.

Close #43
Dropped outdated py3 info from readme
Test Python 3.9 on Travis
Fixed build of embedded program in Travis
Added travis config

Tests can run using tox

Test suite massaged a bit more to make use of pytest

Build works with Python 3.8, so close #66

Build pyrun in the test instead of using the makefile

Makefile dropped altogether. Test ported to pytest properly in order to
use fixtures, simplified dropping further py2/3 support, run through
black.

Tests can now run on develop mode:

    python setup.py develop
    make tests/pyrun
    pytest

Test suite ported to Py3 only

Dropped use of nose, using pytest instead.

If I see another `self.assertTrue` I puke.
Py2 evicted from Makefile
Copyright year bumped
Require Python 3.6
Bump to 1.2 to do some proper cleanup

define PY_SSIZE_T_CLEAN to avoid deprecation warning

* https://docs.python.org/3/c-api/intro.html

This change addresses the need by:

* Deprecation error from setproctitle.getproctitle()
Mention python3-dev package too as requirement

commit.message: Merge branch 'strdup-requires-string-header'
Merge branch 'correct-conditional-platform-support'
Mention conditional platform support cleanup in history

Require string.h with strdup(3)

This change adds string.h as an include to src/spt_setup.c so
the sources compile without warnings.

This issue was noticed in #62.

Signed-off-by: Enji Cooper <yaneurabeya@gmail.com>

Define `BSD` to 1 when the *BSD platforms are detected

This doesn't seem to result in any major functional differences,
but for the sake of pedantism, it's worth defining the CFLAG to 1,
just in case.

Signed-off-by: Enji Cooper <yaneurabeya@gmail.com>
